<DOC><DOCNO> AP890902-0016 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-02-89 0059EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Israel     09-02 0273</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel,0284</SECOND><HEAD>Israeli Troops Kill Two Guerrillas In West Bank, Another Near LebaneseBorder</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Israeli soldiers Saturday shot and killed twoPalestinian ``terrorists'' in the West Bank and earlier killed aguerrilla in Israel's self-declared security zone in south Lebanon,the army said.   Three other Palestinians were captured in the clash earlySaturday in Nablus in the occupied West Bank, the army said. Nofurther details were available in that incident.   On Friday, Israeli troops clashed with several guerrillas inIsrael's self-declared security zone in south Lebanon. An armyspokesman said one guerrilla was killed and two escaped.   Security sources in Lebanon said a fourth gunman may have escapedafter being wounded in the clash.   Military spokesmen said they did not know which militia theguerrillas may have belonged to.   During the fighting, two Soviet-made Katyusha rockets exploded innorthern Israel causing no damage, security sources said. Therockets were apparently fired from outside the security zone nearthe area of the clash.   The clash occurred before dawn near the village of Beit Yahun,six miles northwest of the Israeli border, said an Israeli armyspokesman, who requested anonymity in line with military regulations.   The spokesman said the dead gunman carried a Soviet-made AK-47assault rifle and large amounts of ammunition and plastic explosives.   Later, soldiers showed reporters the body of the dead guerrilla,who was wearing a camouflage uniform. The soldiers also showed threeKalashnikov assault guns, two of which apparently belonged to theescaped fighters.   Israel created the security zone in 1985 as a buffer area afterwithdrawing the bulk of its force following a three-year occupation.</TEXT></DOC>